CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 12, 1958, pg. 1, reads: "Suicide Leap - Frank Palmer, 42, of 1922 Runnette St., Penn Hills, leaped from this high bridge on Lincoln Ave. extension into a deep ravine between Leech Farm Veterans Hospital and the Allegheny River, Monday. A sister-in-law, Mrs. Dorothy Watkins, of 8401 Harmitage St., who identified the body, said the victim had been despondent. Two boys found the body. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Bridge crossing ravine with trees along Lincoln Avenue Extension, Homewood
